\- (each @collection as item) ... (end)
   the loop walks static data — no iteration state, no mutation, no surprises. -\

#findings: [
  { claim - Attention precedes perception, strength - strong   }
  { claim - Looking is never neutral,       strength - moderate }
  { claim - Attention is a form of labour,  strength - strong   }
]

(each @findings as finding)
@finding
|claim - @finding.claim|
|strength - @finding.strength|
finding@
(end)

\- iteration is what makes a Wit document self-organising —
   define the chapters as data, and both the table of contents
   and the chapter bodies render from the same source. -\

#chapters: [
  { number - I,   title - The Lamp,     file - one.wit   }
  { number - II,  title - The Voice,    file - two.wit   }
  { number - III, title - The Stranger, file - three.wit }
]

@toc
(each @chapters as ch)
@tocrow |number - @ch.number| |title - @ch.title| tocrow@
(end)
toc@
